  "text": "Brachypodium was reported to be more closely related to wheat than to rice [CITATION_1] ). The genomic regions of Brachypodium and rice corresponding to the wheat 3DL3-0.81-1.00 were found to be similar instead in this study. Both Brachypodium and rice had 63% of evaluated ESTs collinear with wheat ( Table 2) . The wheat EST BE426418 detected a locus close to the ones that EST BE444864 corresponded to in both rice and Brachypodium (Fig. 3) . These results indicate complexity of the collinearity of wheat genomes with Brachypodium genome. Therefore, local comparative mapping is suggested before using Brachypodium genomic sequences for Wne mapping or gene cloning in wheat.",
